properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 9 at 2:32AM PST until January 9 at 8:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts 40 to 50 mph.

* WHERE...Antelope Valley. Winds strongest in the western portion.

* WHEN...From noon today to 8 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds make driving difficult, especially for
high profile vehicles, including Highways 101, 154, and 192.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest winds in the Gaviota/Refugio
areas and in the hills above Montecito.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 8 PM PST THIS EVENING
